# Timeline Integration with Technical Implementation

**Synchronizing change activities with technical milestones**

| Month | Technical Milestone | Change Management Activity | Outcome |
|-------|-------------------|---------------------------|---------|
| **1-2** | Project initiation | Urgency creation, coalition building | Change readiness |
| **3-4** | System design | Vision communication, champion training | Understanding |
| **5-8** | Development phase | Skill building, early wins | Capability |
| **9-12** | Testing phase | Practice sessions, feedback loops | Confidence |
| **13-16** | Deployment phase | Support intensification, celebration | Adoption |
| **17-18** | Optimization | Institutionalization, sustainability | Integration |

**Principle: Change management leads, supports, and follows technical implementation**

@notes:
- Integration prevents change activities from being afterthought
- Change management starts before technical work
- Support intensifies during deployment
- Institutionalization ensures sustainability

---

